    </section>

    <!-- NAV Erosion Analysis -->
    <section class="erosion-section">
      <h2>NAV Erosion Analysis: The Return of Capital Problem</h2>
      <div class="erosion-card">
        <div class="erosion-stats">
          <div class="erosion-item">
            <div class="erosion-label">Recent ROC Percentages</div>
            <div class="erosion-value">90-100%</div>
          </div>
          <div class="erosion-item">
            <div class="erosion-label">Price Decline Since Inception</div>
            <div class="erosion-value negative">~$25 → $21</div>
          </div>
          <div class="erosion-item">
            <div class="erosion-label">NAV vs Market Return</div>
            <div class="erosion-value">+67% vs +61%</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="erosion-explanation">
          <h3>What This Means</h3>
          <p>Most MSTY distributions are classified as "return of capital" (ROC), meaning they come from your invested principal rather than true earnings. Recent weeks show ROC percentages of 14.41%, 98.82%, 98.58%, 14.65%, 100%, 97.91%, 98.59%, and 93.12%.</p>
          <p><strong>Key Risk:</strong> While the fund shows positive NAV performance, the high distributions are largely returning your own money back to you, gradually eroding the investment principal over time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Holdings Breakdown -->
    <section class="holdings-section">
      <h2>Holdings Breakdown</h2>
      <div class="holdings-card">
        <div class="holdings-chart">
          <canvas id="holdingsChart" width="400" height="400"></canvas>
        </div>
